# Package Manager: Use uv

All dependency management must use [uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/). Never use `pip`, `poetry`, `pipenv`, `conda`, or `virtualenv` directly.

## Adding and Removing Dependencies

Declare dependencies in `pyproject.toml` and install them with `uv sync`. There is no need to run `uv add` manually — edit the dependency list directly, then sync.

```toml
# ✅ GOOD — edit pyproject.toml
[project]
dependencies = [
    "torch",
]

[dependency-groups]
dev = [
    "pytest",
]
```

```bash
# ✅ GOOD — sync after editing pyproject.toml
uv sync

# ❌ BAD — manually adding libraries
uv add torch
pip install torch
poetry add torch
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

## Running Commands

Run scripts and tools through `uv run` so they use the project environment.

```bash
# ✅ GOOD
uv run python train.py
uv run pytest

# ❌ BAD
python train.py
pytest
```
